Brihadishvara Temple, also called Rajarajesvaram or Peruvudaiyar Koyil, is a Hindu temple dedicated to Shiva
dravidian architecture
called as Dhakshina Meru of south.
 Raja Raja Chola I between 1003 and 1010 AD,
 unesco world heritage site
  known as the "Great Living Chola Temples", along with the Chola dynasty era Gangaikonda Cholapuram temple and Airavatesvara temple
  sculptures predominantly related to Shaivism, but also of Vaishnvaism and Shaktism traditions of Hinduism.